        "timestamp": "2018-08-28 17:26:13.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nWe should probably have a check to see if there is a HPA policy when there is a hpa_score parameter in the objective, since the latter is meaningless if we don't have the HPA policy. If there isn't, we should provide a meaningful warning. That said, our implementation should still decouple both the HPA, Objective function policies. Please do add test cases that has hpa_score in the obj, but without the HPA policy - which, although meaningless, shouldn't break the code or throw exceptions.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
